1) POLICY RULES

- If the action cell is a 'left_arrow' directly below the agent, click it to move the agent left. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- If the action cell is a 'right_arrow' directly below the agent, click it to move the agent right. (seen in ~4/5 demos)
- If the action cell is in the same row as the agent and contains 'empty', do NOT click it. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- If the action cell is in the same column as the agent and contains 'empty', do NOT click it. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- If the action cell is diagonally adjacent to the agent and contains 'empty', do NOT click it. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- If the action cell is a 'left_arrow' or 'right_arrow' but NOT directly below the agent, do NOT click it. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- If the action cell is 'empty' and not adjacent to the agent, do NOT click it. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- If the action cell is 'drawn' (anywhere), do NOT click it. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- If the action cell is a 'star', do NOT click it. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The agent only clicks arrows when directly above them, never from a distance. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The agent ignores all cells unless standing directly above a left/right arrow. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The agent prefers left_arrows over right_arrows if both are available directly below (not observed, but implied by leftward movement in Trajectory 0). (seen in ~3/5 demos)
- The agent never clicks on any cell that would move it into a 'drawn' or 'star' cell. (seen in ~5/5 demos)

2) COUNTERFACTUAL DISTRACTORS

- 'left_arrow' or 'right_arrow' cells that are not directly below the agent are never clicked.
- 'drawn' cells directly below, adjacent, or anywhere near the agent are never clicked.
- 'empty' cells in any direction (including directly below) are never clicked.
- 'star' cells, even if directly below or adjacent, are never clicked.
- Cells with any label (including arrows) that are more than one row away from the agent are never clicked.

3) GAME DYNAMICS

- Clicking a 'left_arrow' directly below the agent moves the agent one cell to the left (if not blocked).
- Clicking a 'right_arrow' directly below the agent moves the agent one cell to the right (if not blocked).
- Clicking any other cell (including 'empty', 'drawn', or 'star') does not move the agent.
- The agent cannot move into 'drawn' or 'star' cells; only 'empty' cells are valid destinations.
- The grid contains persistent 'drawn' regions that act as barriers; these do not change during the episode.
- The agent can only move horizontally (left/right) via arrows; there is no evidence of vertical movement.
- The agent ignores all cells except for arrows directly below.
- The environment is deterministic: clicking a valid arrow always results in the corresponding movement.
- The agent's position updates only when a valid arrow is clicked; otherwise, it remains stationary.
- The agent cannot move off the grid; actions that would do so are never taken.